Joining ideas
I've just read the paper written by <a href="http://anjo.blogs.com/metis/2004/09/shared_conceptu.html">Anjo Anjewierden</a>, <a href="http://rogierbrussee.blogspot.com/">Rogier Brussee</a>, and <a href="http://blog.mathemagenic.com/">Lillia Efimova</a> for BlogTalk, <a href="https://doc.telin.nl/dscgi/ds.py/Get/File-43470/">Shared conceptualisations in weblogs (.pdf)</a>.

The first part about identification of posts in weblogs remembers me that maybe they should read a paper presented in <a href="http://www.blogpulse.com/www2004-workshop.html">WWW 2004 Workshop on the Weblogging Ecosystem: Aggregation, Analysis and Dynamics</a> that deals with this: <a href="http://www.blogpulse.com/papers/www2004nanno.pdf">Automatic Collection and Monitoring of Japanese Weblogs (pdf)</a>.  I commented on it at <a href="http://fernand0.blogalia.com/historias/19112">WWW2004: los artículos</a> (in Spanish).

The second part makes me think about wheter it would be possible or interesting to apply <a href="http://blojj.atalaya.com/">our</a> work on communities discovery using thesse conceptualisations, instead of links (<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/cs/0312047">Mapping weblog communities</a>).

